{
    "id": "typeutil",
    "lang": "en-US",
    "name": "TypeUtil",
    "description": "Check what kind of value you're holding (number, text, true/false, vector...) and convert between them — for example turning typed text into a usable number.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/typeutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "typeutil",
        "convert",
        "type",
        "cast"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "Math",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/math"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "Debug",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/debug"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "TypeUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Every value in your game has a **type** — it might be a number, a piece of text, a true/false flag, a position, a color, and so on. `TypeUtil` lets you ask \"what kind of value is this?\" and **convert** one kind into another, like turning the text a player typed (`\"42\"`) into a real number you can do math with (`42`)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The type numbers"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Several methods use a **type number** to say which kind of value you mean. Here is the full list:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Number",
                "Type",
                "What it is"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`0`", "Integer", "A whole number, like `7`."],
                ["`1`", "Float", "A decimal number, like `3.5`."],
                ["`2`", "Boolean", "A true/false flag."],
                ["`3`", "String", "Text, like `\"hello\"`."],
                ["`4`", "Object", "A generic value of any kind."],
                ["`5`", "Vector3", "A 3D point or direction (x, y, z)."],
                ["`6`", "Quaternion", "A rotation."],
                ["`7`", "Color", "A color (red, green, blue, alpha)."],
                ["`8`", "Instance", "A reference to a script or object."],
                ["`9`", "List", "An ordered collection of values."],
                ["`10`", "Dictionary", "A set of key → value pairs."],
                ["`11`", "Asset", "A reference to a project asset."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Checking a value's type"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`GetType` returns the type **number** (from the table above), and `GetTypeName` returns a readable **name**. Use these when a value could be more than one kind and you need to handle each case."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "int kind = TypeUtil.GetType(someValue);",
                "if (kind == 0) { Debug.Log(\"It's a whole number!\"); }   // 0 = Integer",
                "",
                "string name = TypeUtil.GetTypeName(someValue);",
                "Debug.Log(name);   // prints the type's name"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Converting between types"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Convert(value, newType)` changes a value into the type you ask for. The most common use is turning text from a player's input box into a number you can calculate with:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// The player typed \"42\" into a text box.",
                "object typed = \"42\";",
                "",
                "// Convert that text into a real whole number (type 0 = Integer).",
                "object asNumber = TypeUtil.Convert(typed, 0);",
                "// asNumber is now 42 and can be used in math."
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Many sensible conversions are supported, for example:"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "ul",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "list": [
                {"t": "**Text → number** — `\"42\"` becomes `42` (or `3.5` for a Float)."},
                {"t": "**Number → text** — any value can become a readable string."},
                {"t": "**Number ↔ true/false** — `0` is `false`, anything else is `true`."},
                {"t": "**Vector3 ↔ Quaternion ↔ Color** — convert between 3D-style values."},
                {"t": "**Vector3 / Color → List** — split a value into its parts as a list."}
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "warning",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Conversions only work when they make sense. Converting the text `\"hello\"` to a number can't produce a real value, so always sanity-check player input — for example confirm the text looks like a number before relying on the result."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                [
                    "`string`",
                    "`GetTypeName`",
                    "`object value`"
                ],
                [
                    "`int`",
                    "`GetType`",
                    "`object value`"
                ],
                [
                    "`object`",
                    "`Convert`",
                    "`object value, int newType`"
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The type numbers here are the same ones used across UniScript. See [ListUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/listutil) and [DictionaryUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/dictionaryutil) for working with the List (9) and Dictionary (10) types."
        }
    ]
}
